#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:60
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:63
#, no-c-format
msgid "What is &akregator;?"
msgstr "Kaj je &akregator;?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:65
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&akregator; is a &kde; application for reading online news feeds. It has a "
"powerful, user-friendly interface for reading feeds and the management of "
"them."
msgstr ""
"&akregator; je &kde; aplikacija za branje spletnih virov novic. Ima "
"zmogljiv, uporabniku prijazen vmesnik za branje virov in njihovo upravljanje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:69
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&akregator; is a lightweight and fast program for displaying news items "
"provided by feeds, supporting all commonly-used versions of <acronym>RSS</"
"acronym> and Atom feeds. Its interface is similar to those of e-mail "
"programs, thus hopefully being very familiar to the user. Useful features "
"include searching within article titles, management of feeds in folders and "
"setting archiving preferences. Feeds can be displayed in a similar manner to "
"e-mails. Websites related to a feed can be shown in &akregator;'s embedded "
"browser or, at the users' choice, opened in an external browser."
msgstr ""
"&akregator; je lahek in hiter program za prikazovanje novic, ki jih "
"zagotavljajo viri, ki podpira vse pogosto uporabljene različice virov "
"<acronym>RSS</acronym> in Atom. Njegov vmesnik je podoben vmesnikom e-"
"poštnih programov, zato upajmo, da je uporabniku zelo domač. Uporabne "
"funkcije vključujejo iskanje po naslovih člankov, upravljanje virov v mapah "
"in nastavitev arhiviranja. Vire je mogoče prikazati na podoben način kot e-"
"pošto. Spletna mesta, povezana z virom, se lahko prikažejo v vdelanem "
"brskalniku &akregator; ali pa se po izbiri uporabnika odprejo v zunanjem "
"brskalniku."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>RSS</acronym> and Atom feeds"
msgstr "Viri <acronym>RSS</acronym> in Atom"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:79
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>RSS</acronym> (Really Simple Syndication) is an &XML;-based format "
"used for publishing news or articles in a machine-readable form. An "
"<acronym>RSS</acronym> or Atom file is also called a feed. A program that "
"can be used to read such feeds is called a feed reader or aggregator, hence "
"the title of the application, &akregator;."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>RSS</acronym> (Really Simple Syndication) je format, ki temelji na "
"&XML; in se uporablja za objavljanje novic ali člankov v strojno berljivi "
"obliki. Datoteka <acronym>RSS</acronym> ali Atom se imenuje tudi vir. "
"Program, ki se lahko uporablja za branje takšnih virov, se imenuje bralnik "
"virov ali zbiralnik, od tod tudi naslov aplikacije &akregator;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&akregator; automatically extracts new items from the feed and displays them "
"in a human-friendly form to the user. The user can therefore save time with "
"regularly-visited websites, as they need no longer manually check whether "
"there are new pieces of information available."
msgstr ""
"&akregator; samodejno izvleče nove elemente iz vira in jih uporabniku "
"prikaže v človeku prijazni obliki. Uporabnik lahko tako prihrani čas z redno "
"obiskanimi spletnimi stranmi, saj mu ni več treba ročno preverjati, ali so "
"na voljo nove informacije."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:84
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>RSS</acronym> is available in different versions which are not "
"compatible with each other (this situation caused by competing companies): "
"<acronym>RSS</acronym> 0.9, <acronym>RSS</acronym> 1.0 and <acronym>RSS</"
"acronym> 2.0. Atom is also an &XML;-based feed language which has been "
"redesigned to fit the needs of webloggers and news sites. Atom attempts to "
"replace <acronym>RSS</acronym> feeds and remove the uncertainty with "
"incompatibilities in the different <acronym>RSS</acronym> versions."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>RSS</acronym> je na voljo v različnih različicah, ki med seboj niso "
"združljive (to stanje povzročajo konkurenčna podjetja): <acronym>RSS</"
"acronym> 0.9, <acronym>RSS</acronym> 1.0 in <acronym>RSS</acronym> 2.0. Atom "
"je tudi jezik za vire, ki temelji na &XML; in je bil preoblikovan tako, da "
"ustreza potrebam spletnih piscev in spletnih strani z novicami. Atom poskuša "
"nadomestiti vire <acronym>RSS</acronym> in odstraniti negotovost zaradi "
"nezdružljivosti v različnih različicah <acronym>RSS</acronym>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:97
#, no-c-format
msgid "Quick Start to &akregator;"
msgstr "Hiter začetek v &akregator;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:99
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section describes how to start using &akregator;. It explains the user "
"interface and shows you how to add your own feed to the list. This section "
"is particularly interesting if you are not yet familiar with the general "
"<acronym>RSS</acronym>/Atom and feed aggregator concept."
msgstr ""
"Ta razdelek opisuje, kako začeti uporabljati &akregator;. Razlaga "
"uporabniški vmesnik in vam pokaže, kako dodate svoj vir na seznam. Ta "
"razdelek je še posebej zanimiv, če še niste seznanjeni s splošnim konceptom "
"<acronym>RSS</acronym>/Atom in zbiralnika virov."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Main Window"
msgstr "Glavno okno"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid "When you first start &akregator;, you see its main window:"
msgstr "Ko prvič zaženete &akregator;, vidite njegovo glavno okno:"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:112
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>&akregator; main window</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>&akregator; glavno okno</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:115
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>&akregator; main window</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&akregator; glavno okno</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The main window consists of the feed list, the article list and the article "
"viewer."
msgstr ""
"Glavno okno sestavljajo seznam virov, seznam člankov in pregledovalnik "
"člankov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:124
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The feed list is on the left. In the tree, you have news feeds you can "
"select. A news feed is a collection of articles: for example, the recent "
"news of a news site or the new entries of a blog. The default list contains "
"feeds related to the &kde; project, but of course you can add your own feeds "
"and remove the ones you are not interested in."
msgstr ""
"Seznam virov je na levi strani. V drevesu imate vire novic, ki jih lahko "
"izberete. Vir novic je zbirka člankov: na primer nedavne novice na spletnem "
"mestu z novicami ali novi vnosi v spletnem dnevniku. Privzeti seznam vsebuje "
"vire, povezane z &kde; projekt, seveda pa lahko dodate svoje vire in "
"odstranite tiste, ki vas ne zanimajo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the upper right is the article list. It contains all the articles of the "
"feed selected in the feed list (if it is empty, you must first fetch the "
"feed). The list shows the headlines of the articles and the date when they "
"were published. By default, the newest articles are at the top."
msgstr ""
"Zgoraj desno je seznam člankov. Vsebuje vse članke vira, izbranega na "
"seznamu vira (če je prazen, morate najprej pridobiti vir). Seznam prikazuje "
"naslove člankov in datum njihove objave. Privzeto so najnovejši članki na "
"vrhu."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:136
#, no-c-format
msgid "The article list"
msgstr "Seznam člankov"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:139
#, no-c-format
msgid "The article list for one feed"
msgstr "Seznam člankov za en vir"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:143
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you select an article, it will be displayed in the article viewer in the "
"lower right of the window. Depending on the feed, it contains either only a "
"headline, a short summary, or the complete article content."
msgstr ""
"Če izberete članek, bo prikazan v pregledovalniku člankov v spodnjem desnem "
"kotu okna. Odvisno od vira vsebuje samo naslov, kratek povzetek ali celotno "
"vsebino članka."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:148
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Reading an article from Planet &kde;</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Branje članka iz Planeta &kde;</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:151
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Reading an article from Planet &kde;</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Branje članka iz Planeta &kde;</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:158
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding a feed"
msgstr "Dodajanje vira"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:159
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&akregator; provides you with some default feeds related to &kde; - of "
"course, you probably want to add your own feeds. Good candidates are the "
"news sites you visit regularly."
msgstr ""
"&akregator; ponuja nekaj privzetih virov, povezanih z &kde; - seveda boste "
"verjetno želeli dodati lastne vire. Dobri kandidati so strani z novicami, ki "
"jih redno obiskujete."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:164
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Go to the menu <guimenu>Feed</guimenu> and choose <guimenuitem>Add Feed...</"
"guimenuitem> or use the default keyboard shortcut (<keycap>Ins</keycap>). "
"The following dialog appears, with an input line labeled <guilabel>Feed URL:"
"</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Pojdite v meni <guimenu>Vir</guimenu> in izberite <guimenuitem>Dodaj vir...</"
"guimenuitem> ali uporabite privzeto bližnjico na tipkovnici (<keycap>Ins</"
"keycap>). Prikaže se naslednje pogovorno okno z vnosno vrstico <guilabel>URL "
"vira:</guilabel>."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:170
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Add a new feed</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Dodaj nov vir</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Add a new feed</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Dodaj nov vir</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:178
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enter <userinput>planet.ubuntu.com</userinput> or <userinput>http://planet."
"ubuntu.com</userinput> in the line edit next to <guilabel>Feed URL</"
"guilabel> and click <guibutton>OK</guibutton>."
msgstr ""
"Vnesite <userinput>planet.ubuntu.com</userinput> ali <userinput>http://"
"planet.ubuntu.com</userinput> v vrstico za urejanje poleg <guilabel>URL "
"vira</guilabel> in kliknite <guibutton> OK</guibutton>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:184
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The feed settings dialog appears and you can modify the default options. "
"When you are happy with the feed settings, click <guibutton>OK</guibutton> "
"again."
msgstr ""
"Prikaže se pogovorno okno z nastavitvami vira, v katerem lahko spremenite "
"privzete možnosti. Ko ste zadovoljni z nastavitvami vira, znova kliknite "
"<guibutton>V redu</guibutton>."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The feed properties dialog</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Pogovorno okno lastnosti vira</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:191
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The feed properties dialog</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Pogovorno okno lastnosti vira</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:195
#, no-c-format
msgid "Now Planet Ubuntu has been added to your feed list."
msgstr "Zdaj je Planet Ubuntu dodan na vaš seznam virov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:199
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are multiple other ways to find and add interesting feeds. Within "
"&kde;, websites browsed with &konqueror; will display the recognizable "
"<quote>RSS</quote> icon <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref="
"\"feed.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </inlinemediaobject>in the "
"bottom-right if a compatible news feed is detected at the website. Just left-"
"click on the icon and choose <guimenuitem>Add Feed to &akregator;</"
"guimenuitem>: <screenshot> <screeninfo>Automatically finding feeds through "
"&konqueror;</screeninfo> <mediaobject> <imageobject><imagedata fileref="
"\"konq2.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject> "
"<textobject><phrase>Automatically finding feeds through &konqueror;</"
"phrase></textobject> </mediaobject> </screenshot> On pages with this "
"<quote>RSS</quote> or this icon<inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata "
"fileref=\"rss.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </inlinemediaobject>, "
"right-click on the icon and choose in the context menu <guimenuitem>Copy "
"Link Address</guimenuitem>:"
msgstr ""
"Obstaja več drugih načinov za iskanje in dodajanje zanimivih virov. Znotraj "
"&kde;, spletna mesta, brskana s &konqueror; bo prikazal prepoznavno ikono "
"<quote>RSS</quote> <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref="
"\"feed.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </inlinemediaobject>v spodnjem "
"desnem kotu, če na spletnem mestu zazna združljiv vir novic. Samo levi klik "
"na ikono in izberite <guimenuitem>Dodaj vir v &akregator;</guimenuitem>: "
"<screenshot> <screeninfo>Samodejno iskanje virov prek &konqueror;</"
"screeninfo> <mediaobject> <imageobject><imagedata fileref=\"konq2 .png\" "
"format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject> <textobject><phrase>Samodejno iskanje virov "
"prek &konqueror;ja</phrase></textobject> </mediaobject> </screenshot> Na "
"straneh s tem <quote>RSS </quote> ali to ikono<inlinemediaobject> "
"<imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"rss.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> "
"</inlinemediaobject>, z desno miškino tipko kliknite ikono in izberite v "
"kontekstnem meniju <guimenuitem>Kopiraj naslov povezave</guimenuitem>:"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:223
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<screeninfo>Automatically finding feeds through &konqueror;</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Samodejno iskanje virov prek &konqueror;</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:226
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Automatically finding feeds through &konqueror;</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Samodejno iskanje virov prek &konqueror;</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:231
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Switch to &akregator;, select <guimenuitem>Add Feed...</guimenuitem> and the "
"<guilabel>Feed URL</guilabel> is filled out with the link address."
msgstr ""
"Preklopite na &akregator;, izberite <guimenuitem>Dodaj vir...</guimenuitem> "
"in <guilabel>URL vira</guilabel> se izpolni z naslovom povezave."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:235
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All feeds added using this procedures appear under <guilabel>Imported Feeds</"
"guilabel> folder in the feed list, and from there you can use your mouse to "
"drag it to a different folder."
msgstr ""
"Vsi viri, dodani s temi postopki, se prikažejo v mapi <guilabel>Uvoženi "
"viri</guilabel> na seznamu virov, od tam pa jih lahko z miško povlečete v "
"drugo mapo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:241
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a Folder"
msgstr "Ustvarjanje mape"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:242
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After adding your own feeds, you may want to group them in some way, rather "
"than just leave them unsorted. So let us create a folder for the Planet "
"Ubuntu feed we just added:"
msgstr ""
"Ko dodate lastne vire, jih boste morda želeli na nek način združiti v "
"skupine, namesto da jih pustite nerazvrščene. Ustvarimo torej mapo za vir "
"Planet Ubuntu, ki smo ga pravkar dodali:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:246
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select the parent folder of the new folder. In this example, we select "
"<guilabel>All Feeds</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Izberite nadrejeno mapo nove mape. V tem primeru smo izbrali <guilabel>Vsi "
"viri</guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:249
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open <menuchoice><guimenu>Feed</guimenu> <guimenuitem>New Folder...</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Enter <userinput>News</userinput> (or a more "
"appropriate name for the feed category) in the line edit and choose "
"<guibutton>OK</guibutton>."
msgstr ""
"Odprite <menuchoice><guimenu>Vir</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Nova mapa...</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>. V vrstico za urejanje vnesite <userinput>Novice</"
"userinput> (ali ustreznejše ime za kategorijo vira) in izberite <guibutton>V "
"redu</guibutton>."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:253
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The New Folder dialog</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Pogovorno okno Nova mapa</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:256
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The New Folder dialog</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Pogovorno okno Nova mapa</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:260
#, no-c-format
msgid "Now you can drag the Planet Ubuntu feed to the new folder."
msgstr "Zdaj lahko povlečete vir Planet Ubuntu v novo mapo."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:262
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The News folder in the feed list</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Mapa Novice na seznamu virov</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:265
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The News folder in the feed list</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Mapa Novice na seznamu virov</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:273
#, no-c-format
msgid "Browsing inside of &akregator;"
msgstr "Brskanje po &akregator;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When reading feed articles, often you may want to read the web page that "
"belongs to the article: some articles only contain the headline, and not the "
"actual content. In this case, you need to visit the web page to read the "
"complete article. Or perhaps an article links to some website, or you are "
"reading a blog and want to comment on an entry. For these situations, "
"&akregator; contains a simple web browser. Whenever you follow a link in the "
"article viewer, by default &akregator; opens the link in new tab."
msgstr ""
"Ko berete članke o virih, boste morda želeli prebrati spletno stran, ki "
"pripada članku: nekateri članki vsebujejo samo naslov in ne dejanske "
"vsebine. V tem primeru morate obiskati spletno stran, da preberete celoten "
"članek. Morda je članek povezan s kakšno spletno stranjo ali pa berete blog "
"in želite komentirati vnos. Za te situacije &akregator; vsebuje preprost "
"spletni brskalnik. Kadar koli sledite povezavi v pregledovalniku člankov, "
"privzeto &akregator; odpre povezavo v novem zavihku."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:281
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that the browser in &akregator; is not intended to replace your "
"favorite Web Browser. It is meant for reading articles, commenting on them, "
"or following up a link quickly. It is not meant for browsing the web in "
"general. It lacks many features fully-fledged web browsers offer."
msgstr ""
"Upoštevajte, da brskalnik v &akregator; ni namenjen zamenjavi vašega "
"priljubljenega spletnega brskalnika. Namenjen je branju člankov, njihovemu "
"komentiranju ali hitremu sledenju povezavi. Na splošno ni namenjen brskanju "
"po spletu. Manjka mu veliko funkcij, ki jih ponujajo popolni spletni "
"brskalniki."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:289
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring &akregator;"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje &akregator;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:290
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most of &akregator;'s options are listed in the &akregator; configuration "
"dialog. The configuration dialog can be found in the menu under <menuchoice> "
"<guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guimenuitem>Configure &akregator;...</"
"guimenuitem> </menuchoice>"
msgstr ""
"Večina možnosti &akregator; je navedenih v &akregator; konfiguracijsko "
"pogovorno okno. Konfiguracijsko pogovorno okno najdete v meniju pod "
"<menuchoice> <guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu><guimenuitem>Konfiguriraj "
"&akregator;...</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:295
#, no-c-format
msgid "General"
msgstr "Splošno"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:296
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The General tab contains the basic and otherwise-uncategorizable options of "
"&akregator;."
msgstr ""
"Zavihek Splošno vsebuje osnovne in drugače nekategorizirane možnosti "
"&akregator;."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:298
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The General tab</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Zavihek Splošno</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:301
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The General tab</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Zavihek Splošno</phrase>"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:307
#, no-c-format
msgid "Global"
msgstr "Globalno"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:312
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show tray icon"
msgstr "Pokaži ikono pladnja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:313
#, no-c-format
msgid "Display the &akregator; icon in the systray."
msgstr "Prikaži &akregator; ikona v sistemski vrstici."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:317
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show unread articles in Taskbar"
msgstr "Prikaži neprebrane članke v opravilni vrstici"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:318
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Defines if the number of unread articles should be shown on the system "
"taskbar item."
msgstr ""
"Določi, ali naj bo število neprebranih člankov prikazano v elementu "
"sistemske opravilne vrstice."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:322
#, no-c-format
msgid "Hide feeds with no unread articles"
msgstr "Skrij vire brez neprebranih člankov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:323
#, no-c-format
msgid "If checked, hides feeds with no unread articles."
msgstr "Če je označeno, skrije vire brez neprebranih člankov."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:327
#, no-c-format
msgid "Lock feeds in place"
msgstr "Zakleni dovode na mestu"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:328
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If checked, prevents feeds from being moved in the list, all feeds will be "
"locked where they are."
msgstr ""
"Če je označeno, prepreči premikanje virov na seznamu, vsi viri bodo "
"zaklenjeni tam, kjer so."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:332
#, no-c-format
msgid "Auto-expand folders containing unread articles"
msgstr "Samodejno razširi mape, ki vsebujejo neprebrane članke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:333
#, no-c-format
msgid "If checked, auto-expands folders with unread articles."
msgstr "Če je označeno, samodejno razširi mape z neprebranimi članki."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:337
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use notifications for all feeds"
msgstr "Uporabi obvestila za vse vire"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:338
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set global notifications for all feeds. This setting will override the "
"individual notification value of each feed. When enabled, &akregator; will "
"notify you of all new articles fetched in any feed. If you only want to "
"enable notifications for some (but not all) feeds, leave this option "
"disabled and enable notifications for each specific feed using the "
"individual feed properties dialog."
msgstr ""
"Nastavite globalna obvestila za vse vire. Ta nastavitev bo preglasila "
"posamezno vrednost obvestila vsakega vira. Ko je omogočeno, &akregator; vas "
"bo obvestil o vseh novih člankih, pridobljenih v katerem koli viru. Če "
"želite omogočiti samo obvestila za nekatere (vendar ne vse) vire, pustite to "
"možnost onemogočeno in omogočite obvestila za vsak določen vir v pogovornem "
"oknu lastnosti posameznega vira."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:343
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use interval fetching"
msgstr "Uporabite intervalno pridobivanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:344
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this is unchecked, interval checking is disabled. However, if this is "
"checked, you can set in <guilabel>Fetch feeds every:</guilabel> the interval "
"that &akregator; will automatically check for new feed entries. Note that "
"fetching articles generates traffic and therefore may be costly to the "
"provider hosting the feed you're reading. Some sites may even block "
"connections from your computer if you attempt to fetch the feed too often. "
"In general, 30 minutes is a good choice."
msgstr ""
"Če to ni potrjeno, je intervalno preverjanje onemogočeno. Vendar, če je to "
"označeno, lahko v <guilabel>Pridobi vire vsakih:</guilabel> nastavite "
"interval, v katerem &akregator; bo samodejno preveril nove vnose v vir. "
"Upoštevajte, da pridobivanje člankov ustvarja promet in je zato lahko drago "
"za ponudnika, ki gosti vir, ki ga berete. Nekatera spletna mesta lahko celo "
"blokirajo povezave z vašim računalnikom, če prepogosto poskušate pridobiti "
"vir. Na splošno je 30 minut dobra izbira."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:349
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fetch feeds every:"
msgstr "Pridobi vire vsakih:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:350
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is enabled when <guilabel>Use interval fetching</guilabel> is checked. "
"You can specify a time interval, after which feeds are checked for new "
"articles. Default is 30 minutes."
msgstr ""
"To je omogočeno, ko je označeno <guilabel>Uporabi intervalno pridobivanje</"
"guilabel>. Določite lahko časovni interval, po katerem se viri preverijo "
"glede novih člankov. Privzeto je 30 minut."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:360
#, no-c-format
msgid "Startup"
msgstr "Zagon"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:365
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mark all feeds as read on startup"
msgstr "Označi vse vire kot prebrane ob zagonu"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:366
#, no-c-format
msgid "When enabled, &akregator; marks all articles as read when started."
msgstr "Ko je omogočeno, &akregator; ob zagonu označi vse članke kot prebrane."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:371
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fetch all feeds on startup"
msgstr "Pridobi vse vire ob zagonu"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:372
#, no-c-format
msgid "When enabled, &akregator; fetches all feeds right after start."
msgstr "Ko je omogočeno, &akregator; pridobi vse vire takoj po začetku."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:381
#, no-c-format
msgid "Network"
msgstr "Omrežje"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:385
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use the browser cache (less network traffic)"
msgstr "Uporabite predpomnilnik brskalnika (manj omrežnega prometa)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When enabled, the &kde;-wide browser cache settings are used when updating "
"feeds. You can configure the &kde;-wide browser cache in &konqueror;'s "
"configuration dialog."
msgstr ""
"Ko je omogočeno, se pri posodabljanju virov uporabljajo nastavitve "
"predpomnilnika brskalnika &kde;. Predpomnilnik brskalnika &kde; lahko "
"nastavite v konfiguracijskem pogovornem oknu &konqueror;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:389
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You should leave this option enabled whenever possible. Disabling this "
"option leads to increased network traffic. The traffic caused by aggregators "
"not using caching increases the costs for providers and may decrease the "
"number of feeds that are offered in future."
msgstr ""
"Pustite to možnost omogočeno, kadar koli je to mogoče. Če onemogočite to "
"možnost, se poveča omrežni promet. Promet, ki ga povzročajo agregatorji, ki "
"ne uporabljajo predpomnjenja, povečuje stroške za ponudnike in lahko zmanjša "
"število virov, ki so ponujeni v prihodnosti."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:402
#, no-c-format
msgid "URL Interceptor"
msgstr "Prestreznik URL-jev"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:403
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&akregator; can be configured to replace or remove images or frames from web "
"pages that match a series of filters."
msgstr ""
"&akregator; lahko konfigurirate tako, da zamenjate ali odstranite slike ali "
"okvirje s spletnih strani, ki se ujemajo z vrsto filtrov."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:406
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The URL Interceptor tab</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Zavihek Prestreznik URL-jev</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:409
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The URL Interceptor tab</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Zavihek Prestreznik URL-jev</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:413
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For a detailed description of this feature see <ulink url=\"help:/kcontrol/"
"khtml-adblock\">AdBlock Filters</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Za podroben opis te funkcije glejte <ulink url=\"help:/kcontrol/khtml-adblock"
"\">Filtri AdBlock</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:418
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Archive</title>"
msgstr "<title>Arhiv</title>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:419
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Archiving articles means storing the links of articles. Here you can limit "
"the number of articles stored and the method used for archiving. These "
"settings are global settings, used by all feeds within &akregator;. If you "
"want to use a custom setting for a feed, you can set it in each feed "
"properties dialog in the archive tab."
msgstr ""
"Arhiviranje člankov pomeni shranjevanje povezav člankov. Tukaj lahko omejite "
"število shranjenih člankov in način arhiviranja. Te nastavitve so globalne "
"nastavitve, ki jih uporabljajo vsi viri znotraj &akregator;. Če želite za "
"vir uporabiti nastavitev po meri, jo lahko nastavite v vsakem pogovornem "
"oknu lastnosti vira na zavihku arhiva."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:425
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The Archive tab</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Zavihek Arhiv</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:428
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The Archive tab</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Zavihek Arhiv</phrase>"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:434
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default Archive Settings"
msgstr "Privzete nastavitve arhiva"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:439
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keep all articles"
msgstr "Ohranite vse artikle"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:440
#, no-c-format
msgid "All articles are kept forever."
msgstr "Vsi artikli se hranijo za vedno."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:444
#, no-c-format
msgid "Limit feed archive size to:"
msgstr "Omejite velikost arhiva vira na:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:445
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the number of articles exceeds the chosen limit, the oldest articles are "
"deleted. Note that flagged articles are ignored when counting the number of "
"articles: if your limit is 500, and you have 510 unflagged and 50 flagged "
"articles, &akregator; will ignore the 50 flagged ones and only delete the 10 "
"oldest unflagged articles. So in this example, 550 articles would be kept."
msgstr ""
"Če število člankov preseže izbrano omejitev, se najstarejši članki "
"izbrišejo. Upoštevajte, da so označeni članki prezrti pri štetju števila "
"člankov: če je vaša omejitev 500 in imate 510 neoznačenih in 50 označenih "
"člankov, &akregator; bo prezrl 50 označenih in izbrisal samo 10 najstarejših "
"neoznačenih člankov. Torej bi v tem primeru ohranili 550 člankov."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:453
#, no-c-format
msgid "Delete articles older than:"
msgstr "Izbriši članke starejše od:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:454
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Articles older than the specified number of days are deleted from the "
"archive, unless they have the keep flag set. &akregator; checks for expired "
"articles at startup and then once per hour, so expiry may be delayed."
msgstr ""
"Članki, starejši od navedenega števila dni, se brišejo iz arhiva, razen če "
"imajo nastavljeno zastavico obdrži. &akregator; ob zagonu in nato enkrat na "
"uro preveri, ali so članki s pretečenim rokom veljavnosti, zato je lahko "
"potek veljavnosti odložen."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:457
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disable archiving"
msgstr "Onemogoči arhiviranje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:458
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"No articles are stored - all articles are discarded when quitting "
"&akregator;."
msgstr ""
"Noben članek ni shranjen - vsi članki so zavrženi, ko zaprete &akregator;."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:467
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do not expire important articles"
msgstr "Ne poteci pomembnih člankov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:468
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Right clicking on an article opens a context menu where you can mark this "
"article as Important. Articles marked as Important will not expire, they "
"will be kept."
msgstr ""
"Z desnim klikom na članek se odpre kontekstni meni, kjer lahko ta članek "
"označite kot pomemben. Članki, označeni kot pomembni, ne potečejo, ampak "
"bodo ohranjeni."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:477
#, no-c-format
msgid "Appearance"
msgstr "Videz"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:478
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On this page you can configure the appearance of the article viewer and the "
"browser tabs. You can specify the colors, font sizes and families to be used."
msgstr ""
"Na tej strani lahko konfigurirate videz pregledovalnika člankov in zavihkov "
"brskalnika. Določite lahko barve, velikosti pisave in družine, ki jih želite "
"uporabiti."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:482
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The Appearance tab</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Zavihek Videz</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:485
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The Appearance tab</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Zavihek Videz</phrase>"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:491
#, no-c-format
msgid "Article List Colors"
msgstr "Barve seznama artiklov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:492
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Selecting <guilabel>Use custom colors</guilabel> allows you to select own "
"colors for <guilabel>Unread articles</guilabel> and <guilabel>New articles</"
"guilabel>"
msgstr ""
"Izbira <guilabel>Uporabi barve po meri</guilabel> vam omogoča, da izberete "
"lastne barve za <guilabel>Neprebrane članke</guilabel> in <guilabel>Nove "
"članke</guilabel>"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:499
#, no-c-format
msgid "Font Size"
msgstr "Velikost pisave"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:504
#, no-c-format
msgid "Minimum font size"
msgstr "Najmanjša velikost pisave"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:505
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set the minimum size for the article viewer"
msgstr "Nastavite najmanjšo velikost za pregledovalnik člankov"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:509
#, no-c-format
msgid "Medium font size"
msgstr "Srednja velikost pisave"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:510
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set the default font size for the article viewer"
msgstr "Nastavite privzeto velikost pisave za pregledovalnik člankov"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:518
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fonts"
msgstr "Pisave"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:523
#, no-c-format
msgid "Standard font:"
msgstr "Standardna pisava:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:524
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the article viewer, the content is rendered using the Standard font in "
"Medium font size. If you change the Standard font, the change will be "
"applied in the article viewer."
msgstr ""
"V pregledovalniku člankov je vsebina upodobljena s standardno pisavo v "
"srednji velikosti pisave. Če spremenite standardno pisavo, bo sprememba "
"uporabljena v pregledovalniku člankov."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:530
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fixed font:"
msgstr "Fiksna pisava:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:531
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the article uses a fixed-width font in the article viewer, the content "
"will be rendered using this font family in Medium font size."
msgstr ""
"Če članek v pregledovalniku člankov uporablja pisavo s fiksno širino, bo "
"vsebina upodobljena s to družino pisav v srednji velikosti pisave."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:536
#, no-c-format
msgid "Serif font:"
msgstr "Pisava Serif:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:537
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the article uses Serif fonts, they will be rendered using the family you "
"choose here in Medium font size."
msgstr ""
"Če članek uporablja pisave Serif, bodo upodobljene z uporabo družine, ki jo "
"izberete tukaj, v srednji velikosti pisave."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:542
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sans serif font:"
msgstr "Sans serif pisava:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:543
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the article uses Sans-serif fonts, they will be rendered using the family "
"you choose here in Medium font size."
msgstr ""
"Če članek uporablja pisave Sans-serif, bodo upodobljene z uporabo družine, "
"ki jo izberete tukaj, v srednji velikosti pisave."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:552
#, no-c-format
msgid "Underline links"
msgstr "Podčrtane povezave"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:553
#, no-c-format
msgid "Check this if you want links to be underlined by default."
msgstr "Označite to, če želite, da so povezave privzeto podčrtane."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:560
#, no-c-format
msgid "Browser"
msgstr "Brskalnik"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:561
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This tab allows you to customize the behavior of the internal browser tabs."
msgstr ""
"Ta zavihek vam omogoča prilagajanje delovanja notranjih zavihkov brskalnika."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:564
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The Browser tab</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Zavihek Brskalnik</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:567
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The Browser tab</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Zavihek Brskalnik</phrase>"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:573
#, no-c-format
msgid "Left mouse click"
msgstr "Levi klik miške"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:574
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can choose three actions for the Left mouse click action: <guilabel>Open "
"in Tab</guilabel> (open the link in a tab and put this tab in focus), "
"<guilabel>Open in Background Tab</guilabel> (open the link in a tab but keep "
"the current tab in focus) and <guilabel>Open in External Browser</guilabel> "
"to open an article in a new window with your default browser."
msgstr ""
"Izberete lahko tri dejanja za levi klik miške: <guilabel>Odpri v zavihku</"
"guilabel> (odprite povezavo v zavihku in postavite ta zavihek v fokus), "
"<guilabel>Odpri v zavihku v ozadju</guilabel> (odprite povezava v zavihku, "
"vendar ohrani trenutni zavihek v fokusu) in <guilabel>Odpri v zunanjem "
"brskalniku</guilabel>, da odprete članek v novem oknu s svojim privzetim "
"brskalnikom."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:582
#, no-c-format
msgid "Middle mouse click"
msgstr "Srednji klik miške"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:583
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As above, you can set one of the three actions for the middle mouse click."
msgstr "Kot zgoraj, lahko nastavite eno od treh dejanj za srednji klik miške."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:588
#, no-c-format
msgid "External Browsing"
msgstr "Zunanje brskanje"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:593
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use default web browser"
msgstr "Uporabi privzeti spletni brskalnik"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:594
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this is checked, &akregator; will use the web browser you set in "
"&systemsettings;. It may be the &kde; default, &konqueror;, or another "
"browser depending on what you set here."
msgstr ""
"Če je to označeno, &akregator; bo uporabljal spletni brskalnik, ki ste ga "
"nastavili v &systemsettings;. Morda je &kde; privzeto, &konqueror; ali drug "
"brskalnik, odvisno od tega, kaj ste tukaj nastavili."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:600
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use this command:"
msgstr "Uporabite ta ukaz:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:601
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use another web browser for &akregator; other than your &kde; "
"default. If you wish to do so, check this option and enter the command for "
"the browser, provided it is in your $<envar>PATH</envar>."
msgstr ""
"Za &akregator; lahko uporabite drug spletni brskalnik. razen vašega &kde; "
"privzeto. Če želite to narediti, označite to možnost in vnesite ukaz za "
"brskalnik, če je v vaši $<envar>PATH</envar>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:611
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tabs"
msgstr "Zavihki"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:616
#, no-c-format
msgid "Always show the tab bar"
msgstr "Vedno prikaži vrstico z zavihki"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:617
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this option is checked, the tab will be always shown, even when only one "
"tab is open. This allows you to create tabs directly from the tab bar. "
"Otherwise, the tab bar will be shown only when several tabs are open."
msgstr ""
"Če je ta možnost označena, bo zavihek vedno prikazan, tudi če je odprt samo "
"en zavihek. To vam omogoča ustvarjanje zavihkov neposredno iz vrstice z "
"zavihki. V nasprotnem primeru bo vrstica z zavihki prikazana le, če je "
"odprtih več zavihkov."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:621
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show close button on each tab"
msgstr "Prikaži gumb za zapiranje na vsakem zavihku"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:622
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this option is checked, the close button will appear when you move your "
"mouse on the left side of the tab title so you can more easily close tabs."
msgstr ""
"Če je ta možnost označena, se bo gumb za zapiranje prikazal, ko premaknete "
"miško na levo stran naslova zavihka, tako da boste lažje zapirali zavihke."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:628
#, no-c-format
msgid "Open links in new tab instead of in new window"
msgstr "Odpri povezave v novem zavihku namesto v novem oknu"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:629
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If checked, &akregator; will open a link which would normally open in a new "
"window (external browser) in a new tab instead."
msgstr ""
"Če je označeno, &akregator; namesto tega bo odprl povezavo, ki bi se "
"običajno odprla v novem oknu (zunanji brskalnik) na novem zavihku."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:638
#, no-c-format
msgid "Security"
msgstr "Varnost"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:643
#, no-c-format
msgid "Verify URLs using Google's Safe Browsing API"
msgstr "Preverite URL-je z Googlovim API-jem za varno brskanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:644
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this option is checked, <ulink url=\"https://safebrowsing.google.com/"
"\">Google Safe Browsing</ulink> API will be used to check &URL;s against "
"Google's constantly updated lists of unsafe web resources. Examples of "
"unsafe web resources are social engineering sites (phishing and deceptive "
"sites) and sites that host malware or unwanted software."
msgstr ""
"Če je ta možnost označena, bo API <ulink url=\"https://safebrowsing.google."
"com/\">Googlovega varnega brskanja</ulink> uporabljen za preverjanje &URL; "
"glede na Googlove sezname nevarnih spletnih virov, ki se nenehno "
"posodabljajo. Primeri nevarnih spletnih virov so spletna mesta družbenega "
"inženiringa (mesta z lažnim predstavljanjem in goljufija) ter spletna mesta, "
"ki gostijo zlonamerno ali neželeno programsko opremo."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:648
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enable Javascript"
msgstr "Omogoči Javascript"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:649
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If checked, &akregator; will use &javascript; when processing web resources. "
"&javascript; usage has several <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"JavaScript#Security\">security implications</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Če je označeno, &akregator; bo uporabil &javascript; pri obdelavi spletnih "
"virov. &javascript; uporaba ima več <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/"
"wiki/JavaScript#Security\">varnostnih posledic</ulink>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:653
#, no-c-format
msgid "Misc"
msgstr "Misc"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:658
#, no-c-format
msgid "Access Key Enabled"
msgstr "Ključ za dostop omogočen"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:659
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is an accessibility option. When checked, &akregator; will process the "
"web page accessKey property, which defines the keyboard shortcut used to "
"jump to a given element."
msgstr ""
"To je možnost dostopnosti. Ko je označeno, &akregator; bo obdelal lastnost "
"accessKey spletne strani, ki definira bližnjico na tipkovnici za skok na "
"dani element."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:674
#, no-c-format
msgid "Advanced"
msgstr "Napredno"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:675
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Advanced tab allows you to set more advanced options. If you are not "
"sure about their effect, you can just leave the default ones."
msgstr ""
"Zavihek Napredno omogoča nastavitev naprednejših možnosti. Če niste "
"prepričani o njihovem učinku, lahko preprosto pustite privzete."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:678
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The Advanced tab</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Zavihek Napredno</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:681
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The Advanced tab</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Zavihek Napredno</phrase>"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:687
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Archive</guilabel>"
msgstr "<guilabel>Arhiv</guilabel>"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:692
#, no-c-format
msgid "Archive backend:"
msgstr "Arhivsko zaledje:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:693
#, no-c-format
msgid "&akregator; currently only uses the Metakit database."
msgstr "&akregator; trenutno uporablja le bazo podatkov Metakit."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:702
#, no-c-format
msgid "Article List"
msgstr "Seznam člankov"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:707
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mark selected article read after"
msgstr "Označi izbrani članek za prebranega"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:708
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Default is 0 seconds, which means that as soon as you click on an article it "
"is marked as read. You can choose to mark any article as read after a "
"specified number of seconds."
msgstr ""
"Privzeto je 0 sekund, kar pomeni, da takoj, ko kliknete na članek, je ta "
"označen kot prebran. Izberete lahko, da kateri koli članek označite kot "
"prebranega po določenem številu sekund."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:714
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reset search bar when changing feeds"
msgstr "Ob spreminjanju virov ponastavite iskalno vrstico"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:715
#, no-c-format
msgid "This will clear the search bar when you change feed."
msgstr "To bo počistilo iskalno vrstico, ko spremenite vir."

